The paper deals with the problem of approximating the free energy of a Markov random field using a small sample, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also uses techniques from graph theory and property testing, which are common in computer science theory (cs.DS, cs.CC). The results are related to machine learning and statistical inference, which fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
